<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-05-02T14:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-05-02T14:32:00-05:00" n="292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.51/190: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                        Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-02T15:00:00-04:32"><hi rend="italic">May 2, 1923—3
                                        p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>26. Bankers’ representatives today presented to the President a
                            proposition that he grant provisional power of attorney without
                            prejudice to Bolivia’s position in the proposed discussions in New York
                            with the President’s committee. He appeared favorably disposed and it is
                            probable that power of attorney will be adjusted. Committee expects to
                            leave for the United States next week. The Bolivian Government has
                            remitted June service of the loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cottrell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>